RACE.FOOTNOTES: LACIE BE GOOD stalked the leaders in the early going, raced outside around both turns, took the lead around the final turn, drove clear down the stretch and finished well. YELLOW TOPAZ pressed the pace, forwardly placed throughout, proved no match for the winner, but was best of others. PACIFIC VIEW raced evenly near the back in the beginning, showed late interest, proved no match for the top two, but got by REAUX BINA for third. REAUX BINA lacked early speed, moved up on the outside around the second turn, went to the wire evenly and was oufinished for third. PETTICOAT pressed the early pace, weakened and was no threat late. SASSY FLYER sprinted to the front, drove clear and dropped back. BABY LOCKOUT trailed throughout and showed little.
